explanation: This solution uses a prime factorization approach to find the minimum number of operations. It iterates from 2 to n and for each number i, it checks if n is divisible by i. If it is, it means that we can copy i characters at a time, so we add i to the result and divide n by i. This process continues until n becomes 1. The time complexity is O(sqrt(n)) because the maximum value of i is sqrt(n).

